Prerequisites:
	Perl module: WWW::Mechanize
	get-flash-videos: https://code.google.com/p/get-flash-videos/wiki/Installation
	ffmpeg: http://www.ffmpeg.org/download.html


Installation:
	Install Perl module:
		$ sudo cpan install WWW::Mechanize

	Install prerequisite utilities (get_flash_videos and ffmpeg) into system path.
	e.g.:
		$ ln -s /usr/local/bin/get_flash_videos /path/to/get_flash_videos

Usage:
	Put video watch links into a file, e.g. videos.txt, one link a line.
	$ ./fetch.sh /path/to/videos.txt /path/to/output/directory
	$ ./convert.sh /path/to/output/directory